The goal is to trigger a legal challenge to the 1973 Roe v. Wade ruling that established a nationwide right to abortion.
“It is not up to me to determine someone else’s life,” Van Huss said.
Even the state’s top anti-abortion group, Tennessee Right to Life, has opposed the bill due to the surrounding legal concerns.
Right to Life has been more subdued in airing concerns surrounding this year’s bill, arguing Tennessee should let other states fight the legal battle.
“If this bill passes, the ACLU of Tennessee stands ready to file a lawsuit immediately.”The Associated Press contributed to this report.